name: Here's to the State of Mississippi
comments: Ochs later did a version called "Here's to the State of Richard Nixon" with partly rewritten lyrics. After he had already performed it live several times, it was released on 7" in 1974 (A&M 1509-S; B side: a rerecording of Power and Glory ). So far we haven't found a released cover of "Here's to the State of Richard Nixon". However, it has since been performed by various artists at election rallies etc. - changing Richard Nixon into f. ex. Sarah Palin. Also, Eddie Vedder performed a version at the Toronto International Film Festival on 9/11, 2007, called "Here's to the State of George W".
